We recommended the following corrective measures for the aforesaid deficiencies:
Strict compliance on the documentary requirements under COA Circular 
No. 2012-001;
Strictly comply with Section 22 of the Civil Service Memorandum Circular No. 41, series of 1998 and the Civil Service Resolution No. 000034; 
Management should make sure that at least five (5) days balance is retained after monetization;
In case employees wish to monetize 50% or more of their accumulated leave credits (VL & SL), require them to submit justifiable reasons and additional requirements as provided for under Section 23.
HRMO and Municipal Accountant should closely monitor leave credit balances of the employees, maintain and update leave cards of each employee; and,
Stop the practice of allowing employees to monetize more than once during the year.

